com.ibm.team.build.ant.task
Class TeamLastModifiedTask

java.lang.Object
  Task
      com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.AbstractTeamBuildTask
          com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.TeamLastModifiedTask

public final class TeamLastModifiedTask
extends AbstractTeamBuildTask

Ant task to determine the last modified times of directories under Jazz source control.

Required attributes are listed below. Only one of workspaceUUID or workspaceName is allowed.

  • workspaceUUID - The UUID of the workspace context to use. This attribute is recommended over workspaceName because it identifies an exact workspace. Workspace names are less desirable because there can be multiple workspaces with the same name.
  • workspaceName - The name of the workspace to use.
  • sourceDirectory - A directory location in the local file system. The given directory must be the root of a Jazz SCM workspace that was previously loaded using either the teamFetch task, or the built-in loading performed by the Jazz Build Engine. If the directory does not appear to be a valid Jazz SCM workspace root, the task fails with an error. This task is not compatible with the scmtools command line utility.

    All shared child directories of the given directory are processed and will have their last modified time written to the output file. If the given directory has no child directories, an output file will be created, but it will not contain any modified times.

  • outputPropertiesFile - Specifies an output file that will be written to contain a property for each directory under sourceDirectory. Each property's value is its last modified time. The file is formatted as a java style properties file. For example:
    • com.ibm.team.scm.admin.service=200803060309
    • com.ibm.team.scm.client=200803060309
    • com.ibm.team.scm.feature.server=200803060309

Optional attributes are:

  • rawOutputPropertiesFile - Specifies an output file that will be written to contain the folder and baseline IDs for the workspace. This file is suitable to be used by the Jazz Source Control "Initialize Folder Modification Times" workspace action. This attribute and action can be used in conjunction to preserve the folder modification times when creating a new workspace.
  • timestampFormat - A time stamp format as in http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/api/java/text/SimpleDateFormat.html. Defaults to yyyyMMddHHmm.
See AbstractTeamBuildTask for additional required and optional attributes.

Since:
0.6
